comments.body:
@mtrmac 

> If you want to allow both pulling a …:20.04 multi-arch image, and each individual image using a per-arch …:20.04-arm tag, each per-arch image must have two signatures, one with …:20.04 and one with …:20.04-arm

This is the very issue I am looking to achieve. I am looking for the ability to pull by either the arch specific image and by manifest. If I sign the arch specific image, I can pull it back and it will verify the signature. If I then create a manifest using the arch specific image, and sign the manifest, I can also pull by manifest and that will be verified and a-ok. If I then, try to pull down the arch specific image (which just worked moments ago) again, it will get a signature fail on the pull.
